                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.7,
                                "byte_start": 84460,
                                "byte_stop": 119360,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 98-1949, Pegram against Herdrich, will be announced by Justice Souter."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.7,
                        "stop": 229.982,
                        "byte_start": 119360,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15042,
                            "name": "David H. Souter",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/david_h_souter",
                            "last_name": "Souter",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2686,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 655362000,
                                    "date_end": 1246251600,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2686"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32703,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 42141,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/david_souter.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 6839,
                            "identifier": "david_h_souter"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.7,
                                "stop": 14.601,
                                "byte_start": 119360,
                                "byte_stop": 142870,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on a writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.601,
                                "stop": 33.066,
                                "byte_start": 142870,
                                "byte_stop": 216744,
                                "text": "The petitioner whom we will refer -- I am sure confusingly to you at the moment by the name of Carle, functioned as a Health Maintenance Organization or HMO owned by physicians and providing prepaid medical services."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 33.066,
                                "stop": 43.763,
                                "byte_start": 216744,
                                "byte_stop": 259585,
                                "text": "The respondent Cynthia Herdrich was enrolled in the HMO under an Employee Medical Plan and she sought medical care for abdominal pain."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 43.763,
                                "stop": 57.553,
                                "byte_start": 259585,
                                "byte_stop": 314756,
                                "text": "The petitioner Lori Pegram who was a Carle physician, made her Herdrich wait for eight days for an ultrasound procedure and during the wait Herdrich\u2019s appendix ruptured."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 57.553,
                                "stop": 64.171,
                                "byte_start": 314756,
                                "byte_stop": 341191,
                                "text": "Herdrich sued for malpractice and fraud in State Court but ultimately the case was removed to Federal Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 64.171,
                                "stop": 78.14,
                                "byte_start": 341191,
                                "byte_stop": 397093,
                                "text": "In Federal Court Herdrich made a new claim about a feature of the HMO scheme that rewarded physicians with year-end bonuses based on their collective success in limiting the amount of care dispensed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 78.14,
                                "stop": 91.669,
                                "byte_start": 397093,
                                "byte_stop": 451219,
                                "text": "She said that, this was important because the HMO through its doctors was acting as a fiduciary within the meaning of the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974 Or ERISA."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 91.669,
                                "stop": 107.216,
                                "byte_start": 451219,
                                "byte_stop": 513391,
                                "text": "She claimed that when the HMO made decisions about treatment of medical plan and relieves, such decisions violated the HMO\u2019s fiduciary duty because of the year-end bonus provision benefiting its physicians."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 107.216,
                                "stop": 116.373,
                                "byte_start": 513391,
                                "byte_stop": 549962,
                                "text": "The District Court ultimately dismissed this account on the ground that Carle was not acting as an ERISA fiduciary when it made these decisions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.373,
                                "stop": 128.023,
                                "byte_start": 549962,
                                "byte_stop": 596564,
                                "text": "The Seventh Circuit reversed the dismissal holding that Herdrich adequately pleaded the breach a fiduciary duty by Carle acting as an ERISA fiduciary."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.023,
                                "stop": 134.182,
                                "byte_start": 596564,
                                "byte_stop": 621224,
                                "text": "In a unanimous opinion filed with the Clerk of the Court today, we reverse the judgment of the Seventh Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 134.182,
                                "stop": 146.228,
                                "byte_start": 621224,
                                "byte_stop": 669394,
                                "text": "We conclude that Congress did not intend an HMO to be treated as a fiduciary to the extent that it makes decisions about when and how to treat and enrollee of its plan."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 146.228,
                                "stop": 158.867,
                                "byte_start": 669394,
                                "byte_stop": 719967,
                                "text": "Decision with medical components are far from the traditional fiduciary duties with which Congress was concern in ERISA, and we doubt that Congress intended those decisions to be treated as fiduciary acts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 158.867,
                                "stop": 166.106,
                                "byte_start": 719967,
                                "byte_stop": 748911,
                                "text": "Our doubt hardens into conviction when we consider the consequences of allowing Herdrich\u2019s claim to go forward."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 166.106,
                                "stop": 180.792,
                                "byte_start": 748911,
                                "byte_stop": 807634,
                                "text": "First, if such treatment decisions subjected HMOs to sue whenever financial considerations ended into a decision for profit and probably nonprofit HMOs, would be destroyed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 180.792,
                                "stop": 187.869,
                                "byte_start": 807634,
                                "byte_stop": 835951,
                                "text": "Since, the entire point of the HMO structure is to inject cost consciousness into the treatment decisions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 187.869,
                                "stop": 196.08,
                                "byte_start": 835951,
                                "byte_stop": 868865,
                                "text": "Without more specific provision from Congress to judiciary we think, has not warrant to precipitate such an appeal."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 196.08,
                                "stop": 217.317,
                                "byte_start": 868865,
                                "byte_stop": 953815,
                                "text": "Second, even if we accepted the Seventh Circuit\u2019s attempt to limit such an action to a case in which the soul purpose of denying or delaying treatment used to increase physician profits, we are concerned that the claims for breach of fiduciary duty would in fact just turn into the equivalent of State Malpractice Claims."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 217.317,
                                "stop": 229.982,
                                "byte_start": 953815,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "For reasons given in the opinion, we assure that Congress did not mean to turn the Federal Courts into alternative forms for all examples of medical malpractice litigation."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
